The All Progressives Congress (APC), on Tuesday, held its presidential campaign rally in Ilorin, the Kwara capital. AbdulRahman AbdulRazaq, the Kwara governor, led party stakeholders to the palace of the Emir of Ilorin to pay homage before they moved to the campaign ground. Bola Tinubu, presidential candidate of the party; Kashim Shettima, his running mate; Abdullahi Adamu, national chairman of the party, were among persons in attendance. Below are pictures from the event.        PDP CAMPAIGNS IN EKITI Meanwhile, in Ekiti, the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) held its presidential campaign. Atiku Abubakar, presidential candidate; Iyorchia Ayu, PDP national chair; Udom Emmanuel, Akwa Ibom governor; and Aminu Tambuwal, governor of Sokoto, were at the rally. See photos below.        